Anyway, in this post I decided to ensemble a bunch of outfits I wouldn't make myself. But in the end, I like a lot of these looks even though they're totally not me when considering my style and what I usually go for.

Cappelletti Loved it!

Schelchi I couldn't say no to these pointy balls, especially if they're in a statement color. Plus, the smell of new shoes is "prettier than flowers" in my opinion. J.Crew This dress is like a grown up version of a Charlotte Russe dress I used to wear whenever I couldn't be bothered to think. Hee-Lee via J.Crew I really had to work with the jacket selection since the other jackets didn't stand a chance. This was my favourite after L. Spohr I can't but like such a funky color. Poppytalk An arm party sans bracelets. Circus Circus there's something about big patterns and big hats that lets me let my inner bird out. I like the red shade of the pattern on the otherwise grey banter.
